{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,87],"content":"Output Stream Manipulators with One Argument (int or long) | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Output Stream Manipulators with One Argument (int or long) | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,75]}]},{"content":"Output Stream Manipulators with One Argument (int or long)","pos":[645,703]},{"content":"The iostream class library provides a set of macros for creating parameterized manipulators.","pos":[704,796]},{"content":"Manipulators with a single <ph id=\"ph1\">`int`</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">`long`</ph> argument are a special case.","pos":[797,868],"source":" Manipulators with a single `int` or `long` argument are a special case."},{"content":"To create an output stream manipulator that accepts a single <ph id=\"ph1\">`int`</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">`long`</ph> argument (like <ph id=\"ph3\">`setw`</ph>), you must use the _Smanip macro, which is defined in <ph id=\"ph4\">\\&lt;</ph>iomanip&gt;.","pos":[869,1033],"source":" To create an output stream manipulator that accepts a single `int` or `long` argument (like `setw`), you must use the _Smanip macro, which is defined in \\<iomanip>."},{"content":"This example defines a <ph id=\"ph1\">`fillblank`</ph> manipulator that inserts a specified number of blanks into the stream:","pos":[1034,1139],"source":" This example defines a `fillblank` manipulator that inserts a specified number of blanks into the stream:"},{"content":"Example","pos":[1148,1155]},{"content":"See Also","pos":[1675,1683]},{"content":"Custom Manipulators with Arguments","pos":[1688,1722]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Output Stream Manipulators with One Argument (int or long) | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"output streams, int or long argument manipulators\"\nms.assetid: 338f3164-b5e2-4c5a-a605-7d9dc3629ca1\ncaps.latest.revision: 8\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Output Stream Manipulators with One Argument (int or long)\nThe iostream class library provides a set of macros for creating parameterized manipulators. Manipulators with a single `int` or `long` argument are a special case. To create an output stream manipulator that accepts a single `int` or `long` argument (like `setw`), you must use the _Smanip macro, which is defined in \\<iomanip>. This example defines a `fillblank` manipulator that inserts a specified number of blanks into the stream:  \n  \n## Example  \n  \n```cpp  \n// output_stream_manip.cpp  \n// compile with: /GR /EHsc  \n#include <iostream>  \n#include <iomanip>  \nusing namespace std;  \n  \nvoid fb( ios_base& os, int l )  \n{  \n   ostream *pos = dynamic_cast<ostream*>(&os);  \n   if (pos)  \n   {  \n      for( int i=0; i < l; i++ )  \n      (*pos) << ' ';  \n   };  \n}  \n  \n_Smanip<int>  \n   __cdecl fillblank(int no)  \n   {     \n   return (_Smanip<int>(&fb, no));  \n   }  \n  \nint main( )  \n{  \n   cout << \"10 blanks follow\" << fillblank( 10 ) << \".\\n\";  \n}  \n```  \n  \n## See Also  \n [Custom Manipulators with Arguments](../standard-library/custom-manipulators-with-arguments.md)\n\n"}